===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} *{{term||Saxon|lang=enm}}, {{term|Saxoun|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} *{{term||Saxoun|lang=fro}}, {{term|Saxon||Saxon|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term|Saxonem|lang=la}}, accusative of {{term|Saxo||a Saxon|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*Sahsô}}, probably originally a derivative of {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*sahsą||rock, knife}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*sÁk-}}, {{m|ine-pro|*sek-||to cut}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|Sasse||someone speaking Saxon, i.e. (Middle) Low German|lang=gml}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|Seaxa||a Saxon|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|Sahso||a Saxon|lang=goh}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|Saxi||a Saxon|lang=is}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|seax||a knife, hip-knife, an instrument for cutting, a short sword, dirk, dagger|lang=ang}}. More at {{l|en|sax}}.

